<title>FRANCE: Microsoft, SGS-Thomson in DVD deal.</title>
<headline>Microsoft, SGS-Thomson in DVD deal.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-10-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Software group Microsoft Corp and chip maker SGS-Thomson Microelectronics NV said in a joint statement they had agreed a strategic relationship to add hardware Digital Video Disk (DVD) supports to the ActiveMovie platform.</p>
<p>The joint effort will develop a starndard platform for DVD that optimizes costs, functionality and performance for personal computer users, they said.</p>
<p>No financial details were disclosed.</p>
